  "description": "Upload a single image of an object and get back a 3D Gaussian splat plus an extracted polygon mesh. Use a clean, well-lit photo with the subject centered. Leave 'Auto-remove background' on for photos with a busy background; turn it off if your image already has a clean or transparent background. Outputs: a Gaussian splat (.spz) you can spin in the splat viewer, a .ply splat export, and a .glb mesh.",
